wikipedia_page.main: John Alfred Healing (14 June 1873 in Tewkesbury, Gloucestershire, England – 4 July 1933 in Caister-on-Sea, Norfolk) was an English cricketer. A left-handed batsman, he played first-class cricket for Gloucestershire County Cricket Club between 1899 and 1906.
